Description: Terracotta female figure head in Tanagra style. Head erect, hair parted in middle and drawn back but covering ears and contained behind sakkos. Wearing earings. White coating with traces of pink paint on lips and sakkos. Face and possibly back mould-made, but solid, with added earings. Red-brown (Nile silt?) fabric.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Gutch 1898/1899 / Excavations at Naukratis, D. The Terracottas (p. 84, nos 60-91)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DD.629) (Phase 3)
